1x alienware area-51 with NVIDA 480
5x alienware aurora with dual NVIDIA 460
1x gigabit router

all: plug in one monitor
all: plug into 8-port gigabit router with internet connection
master: install ubuntu 10.10 x64 named 3rdi0
slaves: install ubuntu 10.4.1 x64 named 3rdin where n is 1-5

all: install NVIDIA drivers either using the 'hardware drivers' dialog, or:
	sudo apt-get install nvidia-current
slaves: set nvidia to manage xconfig
	sudo nvidia-xconfig
all: enable remote desktop
all: disable screensaver
all: disable idle mode
all: disable "turn off display" in power management
all: disable visual effects (Desktop > Set Background > Visual Effects)

all: sudo apt-get install openssh-server
all: ssh-keygen
all: ssh-copy-id 3rdi0.local
master: ssh-copy-id 3rdi_.local where _ is 1-5

master: sudo apt-get install git
master: install OF
	cd Desktop
	git clone http://github.com/openframeworks/openFrameworks.git
master: run OF install scripts
	cd openFrameworks/scripts/linux/ubuntu
	sudo ./install_codeblocks.sh
	sudo ./install_dependencies.sh

slaves: plug in all monitors with one DH2G on each port
dh2g: set all to only report 2x1920x1080 @ 60 Hz from a Windows machine
slaves: for secondary ports use TwinView, stack all ports vertically, save to xorg.conf
	sudo nvidia-settings

master: get ptgrey SDK, install libusb and 10.04 SDK installer
